timedatectl  - controls the system date and time
timedatectl status		-	Show current time settings
timedatectl show		-	to Show properties of systemd-timedated
timedatectl settime <time>	-	to set system time
timedatectl settimezone <zone>	-	to set sysytem time zone
timedatectl list-timezones	-	shows known time zones
less		- 	is a command used to see the content of a line by being in side the file
ls 		-	Lists all files and directories in the present working directory
ls -R		-	Lists files in sub-directories as well
pwd		-	Disply the present directory
tty 		-	
